## By explaination “Multiple linear regression is a statistical method used to model the relationship between one dependent (response) variable and two or more independent (explanatory) variable”

fit <- lm(weight~height,data=women)
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plot(fit)

fit2<- lm(weight~height+I(height^2), data=women)
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plot(fit2)

newfit<-lm(weight~height+I(height^2), data=women[-c(13,15),])
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plot(newfit)

plot(mpg~wt, data=mtcars)
model<- lm(mpg~wt, data=mtcars)
# plot(model)
abline(model)

summary(model)

set.seed(1)

## Always set your seed!
set.seed(1)

## Always set your seed!
set.seed(20)

## Simulate predictor variable
x <- rnorm(100)

## Simulate the error term
e <- rnorm(100, 0, 2)

## Computer the outcome via the model
y <- 0.5 - 2 * x + e

plot(x, y)

set.seed(1)
